column5: Very last minute but I'm looking for recommendations for a lodgeon Rainy. Will need boat, housekeeping, cooking etc, etc,. Going to be in the area from June 17-20. Any suggestions?
Doesn't matter. Driving up from Minneapolis.--Thanks
Hi Tom-Don't know if this is suitable for you but I have a 3 bedroom cottage on Rainy that I rent out on a weekly basis [email protected] for pics and info
Tom,Here is a link for the US side http://www.rainylake.org/lodging.html#3Thunderbird, Island View, Rainy Lake Lodge, are the three most popular.dw
